content:
I'm running a lighthouse/reth combo for hoodi and seeing the following error in lighthouse:

```
{"msg":"Waiting for genesis","level":"INFO","ts":"2025-03-16T07:16:26.211966828Z","service":"slot_notifier","wait_time":"1 day 4 hrs","peers":"0"}
{"msg":"Ready for Bellatrix","level":"INFO","ts":"2025-03-16T07:16:26.212925421Z","service":"slot_notifier","current_difficulty":"??","terminal_total_difficulty":"0"}
{"msg":"Execution engine call failed","level":"WARN","ts":"2025-03-16T07:16:26.213331554Z","service":"exec","error":"Json(Error(\"missing field `totalDifficulty`\", line: 0, column: 0))"}
{"msg":"Unable to check genesis execution payload","level":"ERRO","ts":"2025-03-16T07:16:26.213356293Z","service":"slot_notifier","error":"ExecutionLayerGetBlockByNumberFailed(EngineError(Api { error: Json(Error(\"missing field `totalDifficulty`\", line: 0, column: 0)) }))"}
```

The API documentation at https://ethereum.github.io/execution-apis/api-documentation/ for `eth_getBlockByNumber` does not include `totalDifficulty` in the output schema, although somewhat confusingly it is listed in the example output.

I'm guessing that this makes this a lighthouse issue.  <@&595683849225240704> ?
